issue.body:
Currently help2man produces some unexpected commands in the manual page file bitcoin-cli.1:
- .TP + .IP for 'Usage' in DESCRIPTION section. Should be all .TP;
- .TP + .IP for '-stdinrpcpass' in OPTIONS section. Should be only an .IP

events.body:
@MarcoFalke, @laanwj 

> Yes, please don't open new PRs for the same thing, but force-push to the old one. Otherwise it splits the discussion over a whole trail of PRs which doesn't make things easier for maintainers.

Yes, I will follow the rules. I beg your pardon.

@MarcoFalke 
> Please squash your commits according to https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/blob/master/CONTRIBUTING.md#squashing-commits

Done.

